WEBVTT

00:01.034 --> 00:04.203
(upbeat music)

00:04.238 --> 00:08.273
♪ Hey, hey

00:08.309 --> 00:12.478
♪ Hey, hey

00:12.513 --> 00:16.715
♪ Hey, hey

00:16.751 --> 00:18.917
♪ Hey, hey

00:18.953 --> 00:23.055
♪ When you're on a holiday

00:23.090 --> 00:27.259
♪ You can't find
the words to say ♪

00:27.294 --> 00:31.430
♪ All the things
are gone to you ♪

00:31.465 --> 00:32.398
♪ And I wanna

00:32.433 --> 00:33.198
- Did you make a decision?

00:35.036 --> 00:37.903
- Northwestern is
my dream school.

00:37.938 --> 00:38.570
I have to go.

00:39.673 --> 00:41.740
- I was hoping you'd say that.

00:41.776 --> 00:43.609
- But what about us?

00:43.644 --> 00:45.077
- Just pack me in your suitcase.

00:45.112 --> 00:47.312
(chuckling)

00:47.348 --> 00:49.014
We'll be fine.

00:49.050 --> 00:50.816
Just four short years.

00:50.851 --> 00:52.584
- Of long distance.

00:52.620 --> 00:54.686
- And then you'll move back.

00:54.722 --> 00:58.190
And until then, I'll come visit,
you'll come back to Florida

00:58.225 --> 01:01.260
and no matter how far we
are, whenever we're out on

01:01.295 --> 01:03.762
the water, it'll be like
we're back together.

01:03.798 --> 01:05.964
- Although I heard
kayaking on Lake Michigan

01:06.000 --> 01:07.199
doesn't compare to the gulf.

01:07.234 --> 01:10.402
- Oh, then maybe you shouldn't
go to Northwestern, I dunno.

01:15.676 --> 01:16.742
I love you, Alana.

01:18.412 --> 01:19.611
- I love you, Kai.

01:22.016 --> 01:23.449
And that's all that matters.

01:28.322 --> 01:30.856
(upbeat music)

01:37.231 --> 01:39.064
We all want love.

01:39.100 --> 01:41.333
Growing up I saw my
parents so in love

01:41.368 --> 01:43.001
and knew that was what I wanted.

01:43.037 --> 01:45.671
But when it came to dating,
I was impractical about it.

01:45.706 --> 01:48.140
I chased the fairytale
romance even when

01:48.175 --> 01:50.142
I knew it was just a fairytale.

01:51.378 --> 01:53.812
- And that inspired
us to dream up Closer,

01:53.848 --> 01:56.014
a dating app that
finds users fulfilling

01:56.050 --> 01:58.317
and practical long-term
relationships.

01:58.352 --> 02:01.653
- Our goal is to bring
users closer to love

02:01.689 --> 02:04.656
by matching compatible
people in close proximity.

02:04.692 --> 02:07.159
People we cross
paths with everyday.

02:07.194 --> 02:09.661
- And, if you're wondering
about our success rate, well--

02:09.697 --> 02:14.566
- We're not just Closer's CEO
and CTO, we're also members.

02:15.936 --> 02:19.004
A year ago I met my
boyfriend Evan on Closer.

02:19.039 --> 02:21.707
For years we had lived three
blocks from each other.

02:21.742 --> 02:24.676
Went to the same coffee
shop, gym, dry cleaners,

02:24.712 --> 02:27.546
and never crossed
paths, until Closer.

02:27.581 --> 02:28.947
- Closer works.

02:28.983 --> 02:32.384
It worked for us,
at least one of us.

02:33.821 --> 02:36.788
Although, I did just get
a new 99% match on Closer.

02:36.824 --> 02:40.192
He loves Tiki bars,
salsa dancing and dogs.

02:40.227 --> 02:42.194
- You just described yourself.

02:42.229 --> 02:43.395
- I know.

02:43.430 --> 02:44.730
And he works the
next building over.

02:44.765 --> 02:45.797
We're having dinner tonight.

02:45.833 --> 02:47.099
- That's amazing.

02:47.134 --> 02:48.233
- I'm so excited.

02:48.269 --> 02:49.902
- Okay, back to it.

02:52.573 --> 02:54.606
What we need from
you at Atlas Capital

02:54.642 --> 02:57.709
is the funding to
take Closer national.

02:57.745 --> 03:00.913
We've been beta testing to
great success in Chicago,

03:00.948 --> 03:04.550
San Francisco, L.A., New
York and St. Petersburg,

03:04.585 --> 03:07.119
Florida, where I'm from.

03:07.154 --> 03:11.323
But now, with your help,
we can take it nationwide

03:11.358 --> 03:14.893
and bring singles
everywhere closer.

03:18.933 --> 03:19.898
What do you think?

03:19.934 --> 03:21.733
- I think, look less nervous.

03:21.769 --> 03:23.402
(groaning)
We've got this.

03:23.437 --> 03:26.338
And if we don't, the coffee
shop in the lobby is hiring, so.

03:26.373 --> 03:28.440
(chuckling)

03:28.475 --> 03:31.810
- Renee, whatever happens,
I'm glad we did this together.

03:31.845 --> 03:34.146
- Me too, now let's
go get that funding.

03:38.285 --> 03:40.519
(golf club whacking)

03:40.554 --> 03:42.454
- It seems like Atlas
really like our pitch.

03:42.489 --> 03:44.690
Said they were intrigued and
would discuss with their team.

03:44.725 --> 03:45.924
- That's incredible.

03:45.960 --> 03:47.092
- Thank you, but hold
the confetti until

03:47.127 --> 03:48.460
we hear something concrete.

03:56.203 --> 03:57.970
Is everything okay?

03:58.005 --> 03:59.171
- Of course, yeah.

04:00.641 --> 04:02.107
- What are you thinking?

04:02.142 --> 04:04.443
- Ah, just that our dates
would be a little more fun

04:04.478 --> 04:06.645
if I didn't spend them losing.

04:06.680 --> 04:09.014
- Evan, there's no losing
on the driving range.

04:09.850 --> 04:11.216
You lose on the course.

04:11.252 --> 04:12.351
- Oh, oh, okay.

04:15.489 --> 04:16.655
- You sure you're okay?

04:17.858 --> 04:18.657
- I'm great.

04:22.663 --> 04:24.129
Oh, hey.

04:24.164 --> 04:27.766
Actually, I have a new
ball I want you to try.

04:32.906 --> 04:36.642
Alana, almost a year ago we
had our first date right here,

04:38.045 --> 04:40.746
where even with just a five
iron you still outhit me.

04:40.781 --> 04:42.147
- We argued about your
swing and I was sure

04:42.182 --> 04:43.382
we'd never have a second date.

04:43.417 --> 04:46.051
- But we did and it's
been an amazing year

04:46.086 --> 04:47.319
together ever since.

04:48.455 --> 04:51.123
We have so much fun, we
make each other laugh.

04:53.193 --> 04:54.293
You're my best friend.

04:58.198 --> 05:03.201
What I'm trying to ask
is, will you marry me?

05:10.978 --> 05:12.844
- Yes.
- Yes?

05:12.880 --> 05:14.012
- Yes, of course.

05:14.048 --> 05:15.514
- You said yes?

05:15.549 --> 05:19.551
She said yes!
(crowd applauding)

05:24.391 --> 05:25.557
Oh.

05:25.626 --> 05:28.126
Um, I'm sorry, I had it sized
off one of your other rings.

05:28.162 --> 05:29.561
I don't know what happened.

05:31.065 --> 05:33.365
- No, it's beautiful.

05:33.400 --> 05:34.366
- I'll get it resized.

05:38.272 --> 05:39.805
- Dad, it's me.

05:39.840 --> 05:41.073
Call me back.

05:43.344 --> 05:44.376
- Hey.

05:44.411 --> 05:45.877
- I knew I'd find you here.

05:45.913 --> 05:48.246
Ever heard of a little thing
called work-life balance?

05:48.282 --> 05:50.549
- Uh, no, have you?

05:50.584 --> 05:53.318
- No, and isn't it
life-work balance?

05:53.354 --> 05:54.586
(chuckling)

05:54.621 --> 05:55.921
How was your date?

05:55.956 --> 05:57.122
- It was incredible.

05:57.157 --> 05:58.323
- Mm, is he cute?

05:58.359 --> 06:01.059
- The cutest and he is so funny.

06:01.095 --> 06:03.462
Wait, you have something
you're not telling me.

06:04.631 --> 06:05.964
- How do you do that?

06:07.134 --> 06:11.737
- Well, I'm amazing and also
you're really easy to read.

06:11.772 --> 06:12.938
- Really?

06:12.973 --> 06:13.805
- So tell me.

06:17.311 --> 06:18.744
- There should be
an engagement ring

06:18.779 --> 06:21.747
on here because Evan proposed,

06:21.782 --> 06:24.649
but the ring didn't fit,
so he has to resize it.

06:24.685 --> 06:26.618
Yeah.
- Congratulations.

06:26.653 --> 06:28.653
Uh, excuse my shock.

06:28.689 --> 06:31.089
I just, I didn't realize
you guys were there yet.

06:31.125 --> 06:32.591
- I didn't either.

06:32.626 --> 06:35.861
I mean, Evan is great, but
it does feel a little fast.

06:35.896 --> 06:37.596
- And what'd your dad
say when you told him?

06:37.631 --> 06:39.631
- I keep calling but he
never answers his phone.

06:39.666 --> 06:41.800
- Then maybe you should
tell him in person.

06:43.203 --> 06:44.836
I mean, Alana, I know you've
been avoiding going home--

06:44.872 --> 06:46.338
- I'm not avoiding, Renee.

06:46.373 --> 06:49.441
- Really, how long's it
been since you've been back?

06:49.476 --> 06:51.143
- Five years.

06:51.178 --> 06:52.677
- Since your mom's memorial?

06:54.148 --> 06:56.281
That's a really long time
and I know your dad comes

06:56.316 --> 06:58.984
to visit you here, but I'm sure
he'd love to have you home.

06:59.019 --> 07:01.420
You could leave tomorrow,
stay for the weekend.

07:02.356 --> 07:03.722
- That would be a fun surprise.

07:03.757 --> 07:05.357
- See, that's the spirit.

07:16.937 --> 07:18.637
- But we just pitched Atlas.

07:18.672 --> 07:19.571
- But it'll take to hear back.

07:19.606 --> 07:20.639
- But work is crazy right now.

07:20.674 --> 07:22.140
- Yeah, but I can cover for you.

07:22.176 --> 07:23.909
- You'll never find a ticket.

07:23.944 --> 07:25.410
- Just bought you a ticket.

07:25.446 --> 07:26.678
- That fast?

07:26.713 --> 07:28.246
- Think of it as an
engagement present.

07:28.282 --> 07:32.884
♪ Chance to say, oh
this is how it starts ♪

07:32.920 --> 07:35.320
♪ Lightning strikes the heart

07:35.355 --> 07:37.923
♪ It goes off like a gun

07:37.958 --> 07:39.491
♪ Brighter than the sun

07:39.526 --> 07:42.994
♪ Oh we could be the stars

07:43.030 --> 07:45.430
♪ Falling from the sky

07:45.466 --> 07:47.999
♪ Shining how we want

07:48.035 --> 07:51.369
♪ Brighter than the sun

07:58.712 --> 07:59.711
- Hey, Rich.

08:01.482 --> 08:04.349
I'll get the usual, a
quart of tangerine, please.

08:07.721 --> 08:08.553
Oh, my God, yes.

08:12.092 --> 08:15.093
(car door slamming)

08:22.169 --> 08:24.569
(Kai sighs)

08:24.605 --> 08:27.305
- Wow, you finally crossed
the Mason Dixon Line,

08:27.341 --> 08:28.874
miracles do happen.

08:28.909 --> 08:31.042
- And you're finally wearing
a shirt with a collar,

08:31.078 --> 08:33.378
so miracles
definitely do happen.

08:33.413 --> 08:34.646
- A minute together
and we're already

08:34.681 --> 08:35.780
back to a battle of wits.

08:35.816 --> 08:37.349
- Too bad you came unprepared.

08:38.852 --> 08:40.552
- So what are you doing home?

08:40.587 --> 08:42.254
- Just here to catch
up with my dad.

08:42.289 --> 08:43.655
- He'll be happy to see you.

08:43.690 --> 08:45.323
He misses you.

08:45.359 --> 08:46.525
Everyone misses you.

08:47.494 --> 08:48.360
- Everyone?

08:49.930 --> 08:51.096
- Let me get this for you.

08:51.131 --> 08:52.998
I'll have my usual
and a fresh squeezed

08:53.033 --> 08:54.299
tangerine for Alana, please.

08:54.334 --> 08:55.400
- Thank you, but I
think that's a bit

08:55.435 --> 08:56.768
presumptuous to order for me.

08:56.803 --> 08:58.003
- Oh, really, okay.

08:58.038 --> 08:59.638
Well, what were you gonna order?

09:00.841 --> 09:01.740
- Tangerine.

09:04.778 --> 09:05.610
But still.

09:07.514 --> 09:09.614
- Don't forget, I've known
you since you were four.

09:09.650 --> 09:11.683
I already know everything
you could ever say.

09:11.718 --> 09:14.152
- Then you know I'd say
that's also presumptuous,

09:14.187 --> 09:16.254
but I expected that
because I already know

09:16.290 --> 09:17.789
everything you can say too.

09:17.824 --> 09:22.160
So why not surprise me
and say something nice.

09:22.195 --> 09:23.061
- Okay.

09:24.631 --> 09:25.830
- Well?

09:25.899 --> 09:29.100
- If you know it's coming it's
not really a surprise, is it?

09:30.003 --> 09:30.835
- Bye, Kai.

09:30.871 --> 09:31.803
- Bye, Alana.

